Defendant Luther Charles Goodman in court with attorney Robert J Hampton.  Defendant Luther Charles Goodman in custody.  Jennifer L Pickett appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Sentencing proceeded.  Statements by the State, defense and defendant. 

The Court ordered defendant to serve 30 days in the House of Correction, consecutive to any other sentence, with credit for 19 days time served. The Court granted Huber privileges, pursuant to 303.08 Wis. Stats. for work and work search.

Court ordered defendant to pay all applicable court costs and fees by 9/19/2017, or to be docketed as a civil judgment.

Filed;
-Notice of Right to Seek Postconviction Relief;
-Pretrial Incarceration Credit.
